# {{ profile_name }}

OSPREY build profile extending the bundled `{{ preset_name }}` preset.

## Layout

```
{{ profile_dirname }}/
  profile.yml          # extends `{{ preset_name }}`; override sections commented
  overlays/
    rules/             # drop facility-specific rule .md files here
    skills/            # drop custom skill directories here (each with SKILL.md)
    agents/            # drop custom subagent .md files here
  README.md            # this file
```

## Building a project from this profile

```
osprey build <PROJECT_NAME> {{ profile_filename }}
```

The rendered project is regenerable — treat it as a build artifact. Make
durable changes by editing `profile.yml` or files under `overlays/`, then
rebuild.

## Adding an overlay artifact

1. Drop the file under `overlays/rules/`, `overlays/skills/<name>/`, or
   `overlays/agents/`.
2. Add an entry under `overlay:` in `profile.yml` mapping its
   profile-relative source path to its destination in the rendered project
   (typically under `.claude/`).
3. If the artifact's canonical name needs to appear in the artifact list,
   also add it under `skills:`, `rules:`, or `agents:`.

## Inheritance model

- **Preset** (`{{ preset_name }}`): bundled upstream, edited by PR'ing OSPREY.
- **Profile** (this directory): your facility's source of truth.
- **Project** (output of `osprey build`): derived, regenerable.
